                <head>177. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>On June 16, William P. Boteler, American Vice Consul at Nicosia, was killed by a
                    bomb thrown by an unidentified assailant in a restaurant in the Old City of
                    Nicosia. Three other Americans were injured in the attack. According to
                    preliminary police reports, there was no evidence that Boteler or any other
                    American was selected as a target. (Telegram 372 from Nicosia, June 19;
                    Department of State, Central Files, 747C.00/6–1956)</p>
            </div>
